		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>To start with, you should pick a race and class combination that sounds the most interesting. All race/class combos can and have been played successfully.<br><br>That said, I think my human SK is pretty darn good. Neptunis paints them in a rather poor light by suggesting that they offer nothing special. I say they offer no weaknesses.<br> My Human hit the ground running with decent int and strength. He may be weaker then a troll or ogre, but hes way up there in int. Many troll and ogre sks cant even summon ther first level pet for lack of mana. (directly related to your int score). <br>Night blindness is easily dealt with untill level 2 when you should be able to kill a fire beetle for its eye. <br>Armor is cheaper because its simply more plentiful in the zones where you will be spending most of your early years.<br>Faction is an incredible advantage. My human can bank in freeport, Steamfont, Kelethin and Qeynos. (So far.) Its nice to hit a zone and know that the guards wont kill me outright.<br>Of course, any stat can be overcome and improved by use of equipment, but trust me unless your well connected, its gonna be awhile till you can get your hands on any of it.<br>Another advantage is that humans level faster. When I began my human sk I also played an ogre sk at the same time. The human hit level 9 at about the time the ogre hit level 7. For a hybrid, everything untill 9 is marking time. And most of the good places to go cant even be touched till your in your teens.<br><br>For these advantages I do make some large concessions.<br>The abilty to slam, night vision, an ogres resistanse to being stunned, a trolls regeneration, a dark elves abilty to hide, lotsa strength from the big races.<br><br>Anyway, it all evens out. No race is better then any other. It simply depends on your play style.<br> </p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
